cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with a control problem of accelerating a consensus algorithm using delayed feedback. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper studies the effect of delayed feedback on the control effort of the agents in a consensus algorithm. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a modification to a consensus algorithm to improve its convergence rate. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses the Lambert W function to analyze the effect of delayed feedback on the convergence rate of a consensus algorithm. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a modification to a learning algorithm (consensus algorithm) to improve its convergence rate.
